name: Barbell Bench Press
instructions: Lie flat on a bench with your feet firmly on the ground.
Hold the barbell with a grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle.
Push the barbell back up until your arms are fully extended.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Flyes
instructions: Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand.
Extend your arms above your chest, palms facing each other.
Lower the dumbbells to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest.
Bring the dumbbells back up above your chest, squeezing your pecs at the top.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Ups
instructions: Start in a plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the ground.
Push back up to the starting position, keeping your core engaged.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Chest Press
instructions: Adjust the cables to chest height on a cable machine.
Stand in the center, holding a handle in each hand.
Extend your arms in front of you, palms facing down.
Bring your hands together in front of your chest, squeezing your pecs.
Slowly return to the starting position and repeat.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine Chest Press
instructions: Adjust the seat and handles on the chest press machine.
Sit with your back flat against the pad and grasp the handles.
Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended.
Slowly bring the handles back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Deadlift
instructions: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell on the ground in front of you.
Bend at the hips and knees to lower your body and grip the bar with an overhand grip.
Keep your back flat, chest up, and arms straight.
Push through your heels to lift the bar, keeping it close to your body.
Extend your hips and knees to stand tall, then lower the bar back to the ground.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Row
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back flat and chest up.
Pull the dumbbells towards your hips, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lat Pulldown
instructions: Sit at a lat pulldown machine with your knees secured under the pads.
Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Pull the bar down to your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Slowly release the bar back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Row
instructions: Sit at a cable row machine with your feet secured and knees slightly bent.
Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, arms fully extended.
Pull the handles towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Slowly release the handles back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull-Ups
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you, hands shoulder-width apart.
Engage your core and pull yourself up until your chin clears the bar.
Lower yourself back down to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Tricep Extension
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands.
Raise the dumbbell overhead, keeping your elbows close to your ears.
Lower the dumbbell behind your head, bending your elbows.
Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Tricep Pushdown
instructions: Stand in front of a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the high pulley.
Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.
Keep your elbows close to your sides and extend your arms downward.
Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Tricep Dip Machine
instructions: Adjust the machine to your desired resistance level.
Grasp the handles with your palms facing each other, elbows close to your sides.
Push the handles down until your arms are fully extended.
Slowly return to the starting position by bending your elbows.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Diamond Push-Ups
instructions: Start in a plank position with your hands close together, forming a diamond shape.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches your hands.
Push back up to the starting position, keeping your core engaged.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Skull Crushers
instructions: Lie flat on a bench with a barbell in your hands, palms facing away from you.
Extend your arms vertically, directly above your shoulders.
Bend your elbows and lower the barbell towards your forehead.
Extend your arms to raise the barbell back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Keep your elbows close to your sides and palms facing forward.
Curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, squeezing your biceps.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bicep Curl
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip.
Keep your elbows close to your sides and palms facing forward.
Curl the barbell towards your shoulders, squeezing your biceps.
Lower the barbell back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Preacher Curl Machine
instructions: Adjust the machine to your desired resistance level.
Sit on the preacher curl bench with your upper arms resting on the pad.
Grasp the handles with an underhand grip and curl the bar towards your shoulders.
Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Bicep Curl
instructions: Stand in front of a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley.
Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.
Curl the bar towards your shoulders, squeezing your biceps.
Slowly release the bar back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin-Ups
instructions: Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you, hands shoulder-width apart.
Engage your core and pull yourself up until your chin clears the bar.
Lower yourself back down to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
instructions: Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height.
Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Overhead Press
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height with an overhand grip.
Press the barbell overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the barbell back to shoulder height.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lateral Raise
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing a cable machine with the handle set at hip height.
Hold the handle with one hand and raise your arm out to the side until it's parallel to the ground.
Lower your arm back down to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Machine Shoulder Press
instructions: Adjust the seat and handles on the shoulder press machine.
Sit with your back flat against the pad and grasp the handles.
Press the handles overhead until your arms are fully extended.
Slowly bring the handles back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Handstand Push-Ups
instructions: Start in a handstand position against a wall, with your hands shoulder-width apart and arms fully extended.
Lower your body by bending your elbows until your head touches the ground.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squats
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back.
Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your chest up and back straight.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lunges
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Step forward with one foot and lower your body until both knees are bent at a 90-degree angle.
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Repeat on the other side.
Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg Press Machine
instructions: Adjust the seat and footplate on the leg press machine.
Sit on the machine with your back flat against the pad and feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate.
Press through your heels to extend your legs, lifting the weight.
Slowly bend your knees to lower the weight back down.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Squats
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms at your sides.
Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your chest up and back straight.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Deadlifts
instructions: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs.
Bend at the hips and knees to lower the barbell towards the ground.
Keep your back flat and chest up as you lower the barbell.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
